The paper deals with motion planning in robotics, which is a core topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Gaussian process inference for online planning suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses optimization and pruning techniques, which are common in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The dynamic nature of the environment and the need for real-time planning suggest a focus on control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of 2D robot simulations and noisy measurements suggests a focus on computer vision and image processing (cs.CV).
